definition.value: An oxo monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of 8-[(1R,2R)-3-oxo-2-{(Z)-pent-2-en-1-yl}cyclopentyl]octanoic acid resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A ketoheptose phosphate consisting of sedoheptulose having a phosphate group at the 7-position. It is an intermediate metabolite in the pentose phosphate pathway.
A peptide that has a carbamoyl group at the C-terminus.
A partially-defined glycan that is alpha-D-galactopyranose in which the hydroxy group at position 2 has been glycosylated to give the corresponding D-glucopyranoside.
A galloyl-beta-D-glucose compound having two galloyl groups in the 1- and 6-positions.

A linear amino tetrasaccharide consisting of N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl, beta-D-galactosyl, N-acetyl-beta-glucosyl and N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosamine residues linked sequentially (2->6), (1->4) and (1->6).
An amino disaccharide consisting at the non-reducing end of a beta-D-galactosyl residue joined through a (1->3) glycosidic linkage to N-acetyl-6-O-sulfo-beta-D-galactose.
